history_headlines.headline: Hidden war against Iran's industrialization. Ruhollah Vahid Kiyani, economic expert: Iran, with a daily production of about 3.8 million barrels of oil, is still stuck in the initial loops of the value chain and instead of widespread conversion into final products, it has mostly remained at the level of crude and semi-crude. Sanctions, restrictions on technology transfer, and the blockage of international financing are cited as obstacles to the development of downstream industries. In this narrative, the historical trade-oriented structure from the Silk Road period to today has continued, and the lack of practical economic operational agreements with large regional markets such as aligned countries has also caused industrial export capacity not to form and dependence on oil revenues to continue. Cyber Army of the Guardians @SEPAH
history_headlines.keywords: Hidden war, Iran, industrialization, oil production, value chain, sanctions, technology transfer, international financing, downstream industries, trade-oriented structure, Silk Road, regional markets, industrial export capacity, oil revenues
